1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:14,252
First, you do a warm-up: Pick something useful: snacks and prices, bus times, chores, attendance or weekly spending.

3
00:00:14,252 --> 00:00:18,831
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

4
00:00:18,831 --> 00:00:26,942
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Create headings in row 1, then enter at least five rows of simple data.

5
00:00:26,942 --> 00:00:32,567
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a useful table heading.

6
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:39,592
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Enter simple prices and apply currency formatting.

7
00:00:39,592 --> 00:00:42,499
Discuss why money formatting helps.

8
00:00:42,499 --> 00:00:45,051
Take one activity at a time.

9
00:00:45,051 --> 00:00:49,592
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

